news.title: No corporate has sought furniture to help employees put in elongated work hours: Godrej Interio
news.para: Corporate clients are more focused on making employees more productive, ensuring that they work as a team and also aspects like sustainability, its parent firm Godrej & Boyce chief executive Anil Verma said.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai up 26% to 10,607 units in October 2023
news.para: Of the overall registered properties, residential units constituted 80 per cent. The registration in October 2023 has been the highest in the past 11 years.

news.title: WeWork plans to file for bankruptcy as early as next week: Source
news.para: New York-based WeWork is considering filing a Chapter 11 petition in New Jersey, the WSJ reported, citing people familiar with the matter.

news.title: Mumbai air pollution: Can't meet 30-day deadline for smog guns, say builders
news.para: ​Representatives of an organisation of developers, along with local MLA Mihir Kotecha, met the T ward officer and other civic officials to seek the relaxation. The BMC had on October 25 released a set of pollution control guidelines, giving 30 days for compliance.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Prepaid meters not in stock, homebuyers can't shift to flats
news.para: "The PVVNL (Pashchimanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited) recently informed about a shortage of three-phase prepaid meters since July this year,” said Yash Bisht, a homebuyer.

news.title: Mumbai: Mhada cancels Rs 10 lakh fee for NOC revalidation
news.para: In September this year, Mhada CEO and vice-president Sanjeev Jaiswal had hiked the fee from Rs 20,000 to Rs 10 lakh “to discourage builders from blocking or stalling redevelopment of old and dilapidated buildings”.

news.title: Bhubaneswar: Second phase of LRC distribution on October 31
news.para: In the first phase, 51,000 slum dwellers received LRCs. So far, 75,000 beneficiaries have been identified for LRCs. On August 28, around 65,000 homeless families of five cities residing in 875 slums received LRCs.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas posts net profit of Rs 1.53 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,578.92 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 7.34 per cent from Rs 2,402.54 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Thane: Palava township residents to get 66% property tax rebate
news.para: Ahead of Diwali, around 26,000 residents of Palava township, the state's first integrated township project in Dombivli, got major relief as the state government finally decided to grant 66% property tax rebate to them.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate posts net loss of Rs 18.23 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Indiabulls Real Estate's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 108.26 crore crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 46.64 per cent from Rs 202.90 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: All stalled Amrapali's housing projects to be completed by March 2025: NBCC CMD
news.para: ​As per the direction of the Supreme Court, Amrapali Stalled Projects Investments Reconstruction Establishment (ASPIRE) was formed to complete the stuck projects of Amrapali through NBCC (India) Ltd.

news.title: Finolex Cables: NCLAT bench 'wilfully' defied order, says SC
news.para: ​The top court, however, closed the contempt proceedings against them after taking note of the subsequent resignation by the judicial member and unconditional apology tendered by technical member Srivastava.

news.title: Dakshina Kannada awaiting government nod for sand extraction from CRZ: DC
news.para: “The district administration has already conducted a bathymetry survey in CRZ areas with the help of NITK, Surathkal to assess the quantum of sand dunes and a report was submitted to the KSCZMA for environmental clearance. We are waiting for an approval from the state to commence the sand extraction in the CRZ areas,” he said.

news.title: SC issues notice to ED on bail plea of Supertech chairman
news.para: The bench asked the agency to file its response and posted the case to November 7 for further hearing. Arora approached the apex court after his plea for bail was turned down by the Delhi High Court.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 72 objections addressed, GDA's 2031 master plan faces board test again
news.para: Officials said that most of the objections were over recreational and other green belts, where people sought residential or mixed land use. They disposed of these objections, according to the norms.

news.title: Revised Maan Mhalunge town planning scheme gets green nod
news.para: Pune Metropolitan Development Authority (PMRDA) officials on Friday said that the sanctions were granted by the Environment Impact Assessment (EIA) authority of the environment department for the revised plan.

news.title: WSB Real Estate plans to raise new fund, focus on South India
news.para: The firm, formerly known as Walton Street BlackSoil, will target the southern Indian growth markets, particularly Bengaluru, Hyderabad and Chennai, for the proposed fund, and deploy two-thirds of its capital in them, said Vimal Jangla, managing partner of WSB Real Estate Partners.

news.title: Vridhi Home Finance secures Rs 150 crore from Elevation Capital
news.para: With the fresh funding, the lending startup wants to scale up operations, raise credit lines from larger lenders and enter into new geographies.

news.title: NCLT admits plea against Ansal Properties unit Serene Residency
news.para: The New Delhi bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) has admitted the insolvency resolution application filed by the Indian Bank against the company and also appointed Navneet Kumar Gupta as interim resolution professional (IRP) for the company.

news.title: Standard Chartered Bank puts Radius Sumers' Rs 569 crore of debt on the block
news.para: The project named 'Harbour Heights' is being developed on 10 acres of land (7.5 football grounds) on P D'mello Road at Mazagon. It will house four high-rise residential towers and a mall.
